original: Hjälmseryd, Jönköp. 1., av kyrkoh. Axel H. o. Anna Engberg. — Stud:-ex. i Växjö 25, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 27, teol. kand., prakt, teoil. prov samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 31. Tjg. ,som v. pastor i Pjätteryd, Hjortsberga, Forserum, Näshult o. Båraryd, som v. kommin. i Lemnhult o. Våthult samt som past:adj. i Bergunda, kommin. i Lemnhult 40.
translated: Hjälmseryd, Jönköping county. First born of the parish priest Axel H. and Anna Engberg. Completed high school in Växjö in 1925 and received a degree in theology from Lund University in 1927. Completed practical theological training and was ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1931. Served as acting pastor in Pjätteryd, Hjortsberga, Forserum, Näshult, and Båraryd, as assistant vicar in Bergunda, and as pastor in Lemnhult and Våthult. Became the full-time vicar in Lemnhult in 1940.
